      • setValue

        public boolean setValue​(ValueType value,
                        boolean forMouseEvents)
        called from getTableCellRendererComponent(JTable, Object, boolean, boolean, int, int) (also getListCellRendererComponent(JList, Object, int, boolean, boolean))
        1. check the value by isValueSame(Object, boolean). if the value is same, returns false
        2. updates value and text with format(Object)
        3. buildFromValue(): constructs TextCellRenderer.LineInfos (buildLines(String, List) and createLine(LineInfo, int, int, String)), and update preferredSize with buildSize(). Also, if forMouseEvents is false, setSelectionFromValue(Object)
        Parameters:
        value - a new value
        forMouseEvents - setSelectionFromValue(Object) will be skipped
        Returns:
        true if updated

      • mouseUpdateForComposition

        @SafeVarargs
public static <V> void mouseUpdateForComposition​(V value,
                                                 Map<TextCellRenderer<?>,​int[]> ranges,
                                                 boolean pressInit,
                                                 Component pointComponent,
                                                 Point point,
                                                 TextCellRenderer<V>... rs)
        change selection range by mouse pressing, dragging or releasing. each rs values will be updated by setValue(Object, boolean) with forMouseEvents=true. update map entries of range and selection-range of rs by setSelectionRange(int, int)
        Type Parameters:
        V - the type of cell values
        Parameters:
        value - the value to be set for each rs
        ranges - updated ranges
        pressInit - if true, it means first pressing and clear ranges and updates both "from" and "to". otherwise just updates "to"
        pointComponent - the coordinate base of point
        point - a point in pointComponent
        rs - components within pointComponent
